hmmm...there is information about that in the FAQ from
the www.junit.org website.  Usually when I&#39;m testing
that an exception is supposed to be thrown, I&#39;ll do
something like:

public void testExceptionThrown() {
   try {
      MyClass.methodThatThrows();
      fail(&quot;Should have thrown MyClassException&quot;);
   } catch (MyClassException myClassException) {
   }
}

The website mentions that, and also an exception test
case, but I haven&#39;t used that yet.

-Eric

